Actress Ada Ameh has cried out following legal suit slammed against her for a job she couldn’t execute due to her ill mental state at the time. ‘The Johnson’ star who in October, 2020 lost her daughter revealed the bill slammed on her and the suit are threatening her life. She wondered if the plaintiff would ever understand the fact that she had mental issues at the time she was given the job, reason she couldn’t deliver. Ameh took solace in the fact she’ll somehow get over the depressing issue and all will be fine ultimately. “Everything is going to be fine. Yeah! I have an issue right now. And it’s taking my life. I no go die. We’ll get over it. “I was given a job. I didn’t do the job because I had mental issues. Would people understand when you say you have mental issues? They won’t! “They are slamming me with a bill, suing me. It’s okay….it’s okay,” the film star said in a video shared on her Instagram page.   Love or hate me, I’m still gonna shine- Naira Marley     New millionaire emerges as D’banj launches Cream Dela…     Social media slowly becoming ‘real life’ – Omoni Oboli